# SoW desktop — recognized .env config keys (loaded natively by Electron main; task 18.34).
#
# ONLY the SOW_* keys below are hydrated into process.env. EVERY other key — including
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY, HTTP(S)_PROXY / ALL_PROXY, VOYAGE_API_KEY, OPENROUTER_API_KEY — is
# IGNORED and warned (key-name only). This is a structural allowlist: a plaintext .env can
# NEVER shadow the Claude subscription, redirect egress, or auto-load a secret. Secrets stay
# Keychain-resolved. An existing shell/CI export WINS over .env; a blank `KEY=` line = unset.
# Copy to `.env` and uncomment what you need.

# ── Launch-tier config (Electron main + the forked worker-host read these) ──
# SOW_VAULT_ROOT=/absolute/path/to/obsidian/vault
# SOW_MANAGE_TEMPORAL=true              # app-managed loopback Temporal dev-server (127.0.0.1:7233)
# SOW_TEMPORAL_ADDRESS=127.0.0.1:7233
# SOW_INGEST_WATCH=1                    # auto-ingest vault watcher opt-in (owner-gated ENABLE, §ARM-18)
# SOW_INGEST_WORKSPACE=personal-business
# SOW_WORKER_NODE=/path/to/node         # override the worker child's node binary

# ── Subscription-extraction arming (owner-gated §ARM-18 — dormant / default-OFF) ──
# SOW_SUBSCRIPTION_ARM=1                # opt-in; env-only arm stays HEALTH-denied until a
#                                       # worker-host-side real checkReachable is injected
# SOW_SUBSCRIPTION_MODEL=claude-sonnet-5
# SOW_EGRESS_ALLOWED_PROCESSORS=claude-agent-sdk   # egress-GRANTING knob (owner-gated)

# NOTE: worker-child ops keys (SOW_API_PORT, SOW_CANONICAL_BRAIN_PATH, SOW_CONTROL_PLANE_TASK_QUEUE,
# SOW_OPERATIONAL_DB_PATH, SOW_VAULT_ROOT_PATHS) are NOT on the .env allowlist — set them via the
# shell, or expand the allowlist (IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN Residuals-18; safety unaffected — all SOW_*).
